reviews.review_text:
Crazy Fingers The jam before 'Life may be sweeter' is exquisite. Donna lovers take note.

> http://archive.org/post/77575/best-crazy-fingers

btw- I liked this source a smidge over CM's.

Phire on the Mountain Phil hinting at the future Fire baseline during the Playin' jam. Very well-played show from one of the most underrated tours ever IMO. I love how they go from Quaalude-slow in the first set on tunes like Comes a Time and Jed to Cocaine fast in the second on Eyes/Dancin'. Donna is at her best on this tour and it shows in several places this night, like Crazy Fingers. Thank you for the excellent Matrix, Mr. Seamons.
